{"id":"a030","internalId":"a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50","createdAt":"2026-01-28T06:53:26.181Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-24T10:40:00.322Z","status":{"code":"PUBLISHED","name":"Published"},"assessmentType":{"code":"CAR_ASSISTED_DRIVING","name":"Car Assisted Driving"},"assessmentDiagrams":[],"publicationDate":"2025-06-04","publicationYear":"2025","ratingYear":2025,"SPRefNumber":"a030","umbracoRefNumber":null,"rescueSheetURL":null,"greenNcapURL":null,"frontalImageURL":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__63805b508e76722e_original.png","frontalImage":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__63805b508e76722e_original.png","altText":null,"width":1144,"height":760,"formats":{"large":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__f4e0fc152cdf8081_lg.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"small":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__a67d6ad6d3790fae_sm.webp","width":320,"height":213},"medium":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__d7631f98eaa29175_md.webp","width":768,"height":510},"xlarge":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__f4e0fc152cdf8081_xl.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"thumbnail":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/a95da814-966a-4b95-b85a-c51a1cc88b50/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030__584bafa9ff1e1142_thumb.webp","width":156,"height":104}}},"newsMarketURL":"https://news.euroncap.com/safercars/choose-a-car/toyota-bz4x---euro-ncap-2025-assisted-driving-results---very-good-grading/s/95cf0682-0861-48b9-9507-bb2c98d07a33","resultApplicability":"all","comments":"<p>Toyota’s appropriately-named ‘Toyota Safety Sense’ accurately portrays the system functionality. The promotional material and the handbook correctly indicate the limitations of the system capabilities. System status information is clearly displayed in the driver’s direct line of sight by a head-up display. The bZ4X monitors that the driver keeps their hands on the steering wheel, and ‘locks-out’ the assistance system if there are repeated warnings. The car’s indirect driver monitoring system detects fatigue but not distraction. The system balances driver steering input with lane guidance, promoting co-operative driving.</p><p>The bZ4X combines map-based speed limit information with real time camera inputs to manage fixed, variable and temporary speed limit signs. The system also adapts for upcoming curves in the road but not for other road features such as junctions. The car responds to avoid or mitigate a collision in most of the test scenarios for automatic cruise control. The driver is supported through the S-Bend, staying within the lane at all but the highest test speed. The Toyota has a lane change assist feature. In the case of an unresponsive driver, the car performs a controlled stop within its lane. If the radar or camera is blocked, the bZ4X provides a timely warning and prevents system activation.</p><p>‘Toyota Safety Sense’, as fitted to the Toyota bZ4X, balances a high level of Vehicle Assistance with a similar level of Driver Engagement. Combined with excellent safety back-up, the system, overall, offers Very Good highway assistance.</p>","testedHandOfDrive":null,"assessmentTags":[],"assessmentData":{"carAssistedDriving":{"disclaimer":"When using Assisted Driving Systems (also known as SAE Level 2 systems), a driver’s responsibilities include monitoring the system’s control of speed, braking and steering at all times, strict compliance with traffic rules, and maintaining situational awareness throughout the journey. Certain situations might negatively influence the system’s performance (e.g. poor weather, faded lane markings, construction zones, exiting a tunnel), resulting in a sudden interruption of the lateral and/or longitudinal support (system disengagement). Moreover, the system may fail to detect certain road users such as motorcyclists not directly in front of the vehicle, or stationary objects. Appropriate fitness to drive is critical for safe travel, even when using Assisted Driving Systems. Visual distraction (e.g. eyes off the road), impairment (e.g. drowsiness, intoxication) as well as unresponsiveness, poses high risks. It is highly recommended to keep your hands on the steering wheel at all times to ensure immediate reaction when the system disengages.","domain":{"highway":"RECOMMENDED","interUrban":"NOT_RECOMMENDED","urban":"NOT_RECOMMENDED"},"nicePublicationDate":"June 2025","assistedDrivingPerformance":{"assistanceCompetence":{"score":83,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":83,"driverEngagement":{"score":83,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":83,"elements":{"consumerInformation":{"score":23,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","elements":{"marketingMaterial":{"url":"https://www.toyota.com/safety-sense/","viewDate":"27/05/2025"},"quickStartGuide":true,"handbook":{"url":"https://euroncap.blob.core.windows.net/media/87713/toyota-bz4x-2025-a030_vehicle-handbook_driving-support-systems.pdf"}}},"systemStatus":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","elements":{"continuousSystemStatusIndicator":"GREEN","systemStatusChangeIndicator":"GREEN"}},"driverMonitoring":{"score":10,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"ORANGE","elements":{"handsOnMonitoring":"GREEN","directDriverMonitoring":"RED"}},"drivingCollaboration":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","elements":{"increaseSteeringTorque":"GREEN","overrideResponse":"GREEN","comment":"System continues to assist while driver steers to avoid obstacle"}}}},"vehicleAssistance":{"score":85.5,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":85.5,"elements":{"speedAssistance":{"score":15.4,"maxScore":25,"verdict":